SUMMARY:Cafe Cursor Dallas
LOCATION:Dallas\, TX
DESCRIPTION:Source: Luma\n\nCafe Cursor Dallas — Build\, Brew & Connect\n
 \nFirst Edition\n\nBring your laptop\, grab a coffee\, and spend a few hou
 rs building with Cursor alongside other developers. This is our first Cafe
  Cursor in Dallas: a relaxed\, builder-focused gathering where the goal is
  to actually get things done while being around people doing the same.\n\n
 No long talks\, no rigid schedule — just a short kickoff\, optional quic
 k demos\, and plenty of open build time.\n\nThe Vibe\n\nThink casual co-wo
 rking with hallway-style conversations. Show up\, find a spot\, and work o
 n whatever you want — your own projects\, a new idea\, or something you'
 ve been meaning to try in Cursor. Want to share what you're building? Grea
 t. Just want to put your headphones on and ship? Also great.\n\nAlong the 
 way you'll pick up tips and workflows from the group\, swap notes with peo
 ple solving similar problems\, and maybe walk away with a few new connecti
 ons.\n\nHow the Day Works\n\n🎤 Kickoff (~10 min) — a quick welcome\, 
 how the day runs\, and a few Cursor tips to get the ideas flowing\n\n⚡ O
 ptional demos (~20–30 min) — anyone who wants to can give a short\, in
 formal show-and-tell of something they've built in Cursor. No slides neede
 d\, just share your screen. Want a slot? Let us know when you RSVP.\n\n
 🛠️ Open build time — the rest of the day is yours to build\, chat\,
  and connect\n\nThe Details\n\n☕ Coffee provided\n\n🎟️ Limited Curs
 or credits for attendees — first come\, first served\n\n🧑‍💻 All 
 skill levels welcome\, whether you're deep into Cursor or just exploring i
 t\n\n⏱️ Come for the whole window or drop in for a couple of hours\n\n
 Date: Sunday\, July 26\, 2026 Time: 10:00 AM – 4:00 PM\n\nLooking forwar
 d to building together.\n\nCalendar: Cursor Dallas\, USA\n\nHosts: Pradipt
 a Shrestha\n\nEvent page: https://luma.com/eikql20a
URL:https://luma.com/eikql20a
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
